column37: Soft-ground bumper winner who was a respectable seventh of 15 in a Grade 2 Aintree in April (good); made a nice debut over hurdles at Uttoxeter (2m, good; in May) when finishing well to go down narrowly behind one who has since completed a hat-trick; should be on the scene.

column4: Wasdell Group Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race) (Div I)

column37: £72,000 3yo; fifth foal; half-brother to French winners Extra Lida (2m4f chase) and Happyboum Lida (2m1f chase); dam unraced half-sister to winners Rhialco (smart French 2m1f-2m7f hurdle/chase) and Qhilimar (useful 2m1f-3m2f chase); given connections, he would command respect if at all strong in the betting.
